{
  "texts": [
    "In this case, factor neutrality means that the portfolio beta matches the benchmark beta for that factor.",
    "This also is a linear equality constraint that can be expressed as β i = β b i, with β b the benchmark betas.",
    "Advantages of a factor model.",
    "Especially with large universes, the factor model (specified by F, Σ f, and D) can give a better estimate of the return covariance, compared to methods that directly estimate the n × n matrix Σ [JOP + 23].",
    "Another substantial advantage is computational."
  ]
